{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XZ3Epx6z9r5oRDLC68f81F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks completed. Here's a summary of what was implemented for US-019:\n\n## Summary\n\n**US-019: Cell-flag wake propagation kernel** - implemented and tested.\n\n### Files changed:\n- **`physics/kernels/common.cuh`** — Added `SET_JUST_WOKE(p)` and `CLEAR_JUST_WOKE(p)` macros\n- **`physics/kernels/integrate.cu`** — Set `SET_JUST_WOKE` flag when a sleeping particle's hysteresis wake condition triggers\n- **`physics/kernels/wake.cu`** (new) — Three CUDA kernels:\n  - `K_MarkWakeCells`: Phase 1 — just-woke particles `atomicOr(1)` on 3x3x3 neighbor cells\n  - `K_WakeSleepers`: Phase 2 — sleeping particles in flagged cells clear SLEEPING and reset counter\n  - `K_ClearJustWoke`: Phase 3 — clear JUST_WOKE flag from all particles\n- **`wake.py`** (new) — Python wrapper with individual kernel launchers + `run_wake_propagation()` convenience function\n- **`simulation.py`** — Added wake module import, `cell_wake_flags` allocation, and wake propagation after Integrate\n- **`test_wake.py`** (new) — 17 integration tests, all passing\n- **`.ralph-tui/progress.md`** — Updated with learnings\n\n### Test results:\n- All 17 new wake tests pass\n- All 29 existing integrate tests pass (no regression from `SET_JUST_WOKE` change)\n- 500K particle stress test passes with correct wake propagation\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":411,"cache_read_input_tokens":115601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":411},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82fdfead-6b83-4a9f-940a-980a5fc302e9","uuid":"fe46b13b-243a-4115-9e60-280dd8a2acd7"}
